%2C%20bark%20papers%2C%20plastics%2C%20vellum%2C%20or%20leather%2C%20fabric%2C%20wood%2C%20and%20canvas.%20Watercolor%20paper%20is%20often%20made%20entirely%20or%20partially%20with%20cotton%2C%20which%20gives%20a%20good%20texture%20and%20minimizes%20distortion%20when%20wet.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22images%22%3A%227413%22%7D%2C%7B%22name%22%3A%22Plastic%22%2C%22description%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOil%20painting%20is%20the%20process%20of%20painting%20with%20pigments%20with%20a%20medium%20of%20drying%20oil%20as%20the%20binder.%20Commonly%20used%20drying%20oils%20include%20linseed%20oil%2C%20poppy%20seed%20oil%2C%20walnut%20oil%2C%20and%20safflower%20oil.%20The%20choice%20of%20oil%20imparts%20a%20range%20of%20properties%20to%20the%20oil%20paint%2C%20such%20as%20the%20amount%20of%20yellowing%20or%20drying%20time.%20Certain%20differences%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20oil%2C%20are%20also%20visible%20in%20the%20sheen%20of%20the%20paints.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22images%22%3A%227413%22%7D%2C%7B%22name%22%3A%22Wooden%22%2C%22description%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAcrylic%20paint%20is%20a%20fast-drying%20paint%20made%20of%20pigment%20suspended%20in%20acrylic%20polymer%20emulsion.%20Acrylic%20paints%20are%20water-soluble%2C%20but%20become%20water-resistant%20when%20dry.%20Depending%20on%20how%20much%20the%20paint%20is%20diluted%20with%20water%2C%20or%20modified%20with%20acrylic%20gels%2C%20media%2C%20or%20pastes%2C%20the%20finished%20acrylic%20painting%20can%20resemble%20a%20watercolor%20or%20an%20oil%20painting%2C%20or%20have%20its%20own%20unique%20characteristics%20not%20attainable%20with%20other%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22images%22%3A%227413%22%7D%2C%7B%22name%22%3A%22Steel%22%2C%22description%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThey%20portray%20intense%2C%20haunting%20themes%2C%20reflective%20of%20both%20his%20fear%20of%20insanity%20and%20his%20bleak%20outlook%20on%20humanity.%20The%20paintings%20originally%20were%20painted%20as%20murals%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20the%20house%2C%20later%20being%20hacked%20off%20the%20walls%20and%20